## Summary Table of Successes and Failures

| Aspect           | Successes                                                                 | Failures                                                                                      |
|------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Political**    | - Reunification of Union<br>- 13th, 14th, 15th Amendments<br>- African American political participation | - Weak enforcement of civil rights<br>- Rise of KKK and white supremacist violence<br>- Political corruption and instability |
| **Social**       | - Freedom and citizenship for African Americans<br>- Establishment of schools and colleges<br>- Freedmen’s Bureau aid | - Black Codes and segregation<br>- Social violence and intimidation<br>- Persistent racial prejudice |
| **Economic**     | - Some rebuilding of Southern infrastructure<br>- Limited employment opportunities | - Sharecropping debt cycles<br>- No land redistribution<br>- Economic depression and reduced support |

